Do NOT create final production workflows
Video Processing Requirements
Frame Extraction

Recommended:

extract frame every 2–5 seconds
additionally capture:
scene changes
UI changes
alarm appearance
menu transitions
diagrams
workflow transitions

Prioritize:

RMS screens
WCS screens
Ignition screens
alarms/errors
service states
AGV maps
workflow dashboards
troubleshooting actions
OCR Requirements

OCR all visible text from:

dashboards
HMIs
RMS
alarms
menus
dialogs
service states
logs
diagrams

Preserve:

capitalization
codes
alarm text
identifiers
Chunking Rules

Do NOT create giant transcript chunks.

Preferred chunk size:

15–60 seconds
one coherent operational topic

Good:

“Restarting Optisweep service”
“Checking AGV mapping”
“Heartbeat validation”

Bad:

“Entire 20-minute video summary”
Important Constraints

Do NOT:

build final workflows
auto-approve procedures
infer unsupported troubleshooting logic
classify root causes unless explicitly stated
remove timestamps
discard visual evidence
overwrite transcript wording unnecessarily
Output Quality Standard

Outputs must be:

operationally useful
retrieval-ready
traceable
timestamped
structured
reusable
future-proof for:
RAG
workflow authoring
ML training
knowledge graph ingestion
Phase 0 Scope Boundary

This system is NOT:

a production ingestion pipeline
a live connector system
an autonomous workflow authoring engine

This is a Phase 0 structured extraction system for manually processed training videos.

Prefer:

correctness
traceability
structure
evidence preservation

over:

speed
summarization
aggressive inference
Final Instruction

When uncertain:

preserve evidence
lower confidence
mark for review
avoid assumptions

Never present inferred operational conclusions as validated truth unless explicitly confirmed by the training material.